['text':'*
 * Provides a hook to check that shards' storage catalogs and catalog caches are consistent
 * with the sharding catalog on the config server.
 *
 * The hook currently checks that: if the sharding catalog says a shard owns chunks for a sharded
 * collection, then the shard has an entry for the collection
 * - in its storage catalog, with the same UUID as the collection has in the sharding catalog
 * - in its catalog cache, with the same UUID as the collection has in the sharding catalog
 *
 * TODO (SERVER-33253): extend the hook to add consistency checks for collection indexes and options
 ','line_number':1,'multiline':True]['text':' A test may want to skip the consistency checks for a few reasons:','line_number':14,'multiline':False]['text':' 1)  The checks are performed against shard and config primaries, and the connections','line_number':15,'multiline':False]['text':'     cached on ShardingTest are used. So, tests that end with a different (or no) shard or','line_number':16,'multiline':False]['text':'     config primary should skip the checks.','line_number':17,'multiline':False]['text':' 2) The sharding catalog is read from the config server via mongos, so tests that cause','line_number':18,'multiline':False]['text':'    the config primary to be unreachable from mongos should skip the checks.','line_number':19,'multiline':False]['text':' When a shard takes or loses ownership of a chunk (through shardCollection, moveChunk, or','line_number':26,'multiline':False]['text':' dropCollection), a best-effort is made to make the shard refresh its routing table cache.','line_number':27,'multiline':False]['text':' But since sharding catalog changes are not transactional, it's possible the shard's','line_number':28,'multiline':False]['text':' catalog cache will be stale. A test or suite that induces stepdowns or otherwise makes it','line_number':29,'multiline':False]['text':' likely that this "best-effort" will fail should skip checks for only the catalog caches.','line_number':30,'multiline':False]['text':' If this shard is standalone, the replica set object will be null. In that case, we','line_number':41,'multiline':False]['text':' will just skip.','line_number':42,'multiline':False]['text':' Read from config.collections, config.shards, and config.chunks to construct a picture','line_number':69,'multiline':False]['text':' of which shards own data for which collections, and what the UUIDs for those collections','line_number':70,'multiline':False]['text':' are.','line_number':71,'multiline':False]['text':' The ShardingTest object maintains a connection to each shard in its _connections array,','line_number':101,'multiline':False]['text':' where each connection is tagged with the shard's connection string in a 'host' field.','line_number':102,'multiline':False]['text':' Create a reverse mapping of connection string to connection to efficiently retrieve a','line_number':103,'multiline':False]['text':' connection by connection string.','line_number':104,'multiline':False]['text':' Finish replication on all shards (if they are replica sets).','line_number':111,'multiline':False]['text':' A connection the shard may not be cached in ShardingTest if the shard was added','line_number':120,'multiline':False]['text':' manually to the cluster by the test.','line_number':121,'multiline':False]['text':' Wait for the shard to finish writing its last refresh to disk.','line_number':147,'multiline':False]